Kira Makagon: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 8:50 AM ET
Software

Company Overview of RingCentral, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Kira   Makagon  Executive Vice President of Innovation, RingCentral, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships54$2,086,617As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Ms. Kira Makagon has been an Executive Vice President of Innovation at RingCentral, Inc. since August 2012, leads global product strategy, product management, engineering and operations. Ms. Makagon served as the President of Ventures & Alliances at Exigen, Inc. from 2001 to 2005. She served as a Senior Vice President at Ring Central. Prior to that, from 2001 to August 2006, she served in various roles at Exigen Group, including President, Ventures and Alliances and ... Executive Vice President, Marketing and Business Development. As part of her responsibilities, Ms. Makagon led marketing strategy, demand creation and awareness. She is highly accomplished executive and entrepreneur with over 25 years of technology industry experience. She served as the President of CoreAudience. She has a strong background both as a seasoned executive focused on driving innovation as well as an entrepreneur capitalizing on emerging industry trends. Ms. Makagon was the Co-Founder Red Aril Inc., served as its Chief Product Officer from January 2012 to July 2012; President from April 2010 to December 2011 and Chief Executive Officer from June 2009 to April 2010. From January 2009 to May 2009, Ms. Makagon served as a consultant of NebuAd, Inc. From August 2008 to December 2008, she served as Chief Executive Officer of NebuAd and from September 2006 to July 2008, she co-founded and served as President of NebuAd. She also served at Sagus Capital Partners LLC. Previously, she was a Co-Founder and Senior Vice President and Executive Vice President of Products at Octane Software, where she had the overall responsibility for product development, marketing and strategy. Following the merger, she became the Chief Technology Officer at E.piphany. She founded CoreAudience and served as its Chief Product Officer. From 1993 to 1998, she served as Vice President of Product Development and Engineering at Scopus Technology, where she guided three generations of CRM products to market en route to the company's successful IPO and subsequent purchase by Siebel Systems. She is a "serial entrepreneur" on her third successful fast-growth startup spanning a career of 20 years in Silicon Valley. Ms. Makagon is a Member of Business Advisory Council of Illuminate Ventures. She has been Director of Calix, Inc. since July 20, 2017. Ms. Makagon serves as a Director at Airframe Business Software. She serves as a Director at Exigen Group, where she has been a critical executive in guiding strategy, alliances and joint ventures. She also serves as a Director of Exigen, Inc. She serves as a Director and Advisor to several high technology startups. She served as a Director of Blazent, Inc., She served as a Director of Octane Software and CoreAudience. She served as a Member of the Advisory Board at 4medica Inc. She served as a board member of NebuAd, Inc. She is a well-respected speaker and Analyst on the evolution and trends for software improving the customer sales, support and fulfillment processes within global enterprises. Ms. Makagon is an M.B.A. from HAAS Business School at the University of California at Berkeley and holds a B.S. from the University of California at Berkeley.Read Full Background




